22:16.556 --> 22:22.522
And here, the sacrificial system is set up to bring the best animal that was pure and perfect.

22:23.123 --> 22:34.034
And when I turn my attention to an idol, something other than God, and I give it the best of who I am, that tells me that it is obscuring and competing.

22:34.338 --> 22:38.623
in my relationship with the Lord, if I give it the best of who I am.

22:38.643 --> 22:43.008
Ezekiel has some really striking language about idolatry.

22:43.829 --> 22:52.359
In Ezekiel chapter 16, verse 32, he says, you adulterous wife, you prefer strangers to your own husband.

22:53.260 --> 22:58.867
All prostitutes receives gifts, but you give gifts to all your lovers.

22:59.808 --> 23:01.650
I mean, that is devastating.

23:02.722 --> 23:09.271
He says, bribing them to come to you from everywhere for your illicit favors.

23:10.553 --> 23:19.565
So something is an idol that we give as a gift to someone other than God and it obscures him.

23:20.887 --> 23:31.602
The fourth thing is to understand what makes something an idol is that it moves out of the arena of just something that we have in our lives.

23:31.970 --> 23:38.498
into something that eventually takes over our lives and we protect it with rationalizations and excuses.

23:39.579 --> 23:43.824
It's always protected with rationalizations and excuses.

23:45.226 --> 23:48.470
Listen to what Aaron said when Moses confronted him on what he had done.

23:48.530 --> 23:53.255
In verse 22, Aaron said, do not let your anger burn against me.

23:53.796 --> 23:56.199
You know the people, they're bent on evil.

23:56.499 --> 23:57.821
They made me do it, Moses.

23:57.921 --> 23:58.962
I didn't want to do it.

23:59.298 --> 24:04.325
And then verse 24, he says, I took the gold and threw it in the fire and wow, out came this calf.

24:05.226 --> 24:07.549
And as we talked about, that's a ludicrous story.

24:07.589 --> 24:18.825
We laugh at it, but the truth is that our own idols can be wrapped in just as crazy a narrative as this story that Aaron tells Moses, right?

24:18.885 --> 24:20.427
That it's not believable.

24:20.487 --> 24:28.178
When our kids were little and sometimes they would tell me a story that was just so fantastic that I knew that there was no chance that that stored that

24:28.290 --> 24:36.340
thing ever actually happened, I would tell them, and I'd be careful about telling somebody that in public, because you'll look like a nut, right?

24:36.921 --> 24:40.145
I mean, nobody's buying what you're selling there, chief, you know.

24:42.407 --> 24:44.089
And here is the same kind of thing.

24:44.129 --> 24:50.878
It's a ludicrous story, but it's still wrapped in rationalization and excuse.

24:52.119 --> 24:54.322
And so think about those four things.

24:54.562 --> 24:59.830
that make an idol as we think about what are some idols that we deal with today.

24:59.890 --> 25:01.713
And these are surface idols.

25:01.773 --> 25:05.178
Now, surface idols are those that are on the surface of our lives.

25:05.979 --> 25:09.424
They're the outward expression of a root idol.

25:10.426 --> 25:17.637
So for example, a surface idol is, I have to have a particular kind of look or body image.

25:17.997 --> 25:20.280
That's image idolatry, right?

25:20.301 --> 25:22.844
We all know this is not bad to care about our bodies.

25:22.944 --> 25:23.986
First Corinthians,

25:24.098 --> 25:30.965
6, 1 Corinthians 9, 1 Timothy 4, talk about the value of taking care of ourselves.

25:31.426 --> 25:32.387
We understand that.

25:32.467 --> 25:33.328
It's a good thing.

25:33.368 --> 25:35.390
There's nothing wrong with wanting to be in shape.

25:35.410 --> 25:37.332
There's nothing wrong with wanting to be healthy.

25:37.773 --> 25:43.198
But the problem is it makes a really lousy God, right?

25:43.399 --> 25:49.525
Because so much of who we are is determined by our genes that we don't have a say in.

25:51.768 --> 25:53.970
The second one is a work idolatry.

25:54.658 --> 25:56.921
I'm highly productive and I get a lot done.

25:56.961 --> 26:01.609
Again, the scripture says that we are supposed to be hard workers.

26:02.630 --> 26:07.397
The Bible discusses the value and the importance of being productive and working hard.

26:08.058 --> 26:14.127
In verses like in Colossians 3 and Proverbs 14 and Ephesians 5 and Matthew 6.

26:15.249 --> 26:21.118
But the issue is when your identity is completely wrapped up in getting things done.

26:22.200 --> 26:23.762
It becomes who you are.

26:24.674 --> 26:25.034
Right?

26:25.575 --> 26:30.282
And your identity is associated with work, only work.

26:30.302 --> 26:37.371
And you take pride in being highly productive and getting lots of stuff done, which is a great thing, but it can go too far.

26:39.154 --> 26:39.414
Right?

26:40.495 --> 26:48.967
The issue is when your identity is found and being able to get things done, and when that becomes the ultimate part of your life, you're showing up to the wrong altar.

26:51.430 --> 26:54.194
Another one is helping idolatry.

26:55.202 --> 26:58.185
People are dependent on me and they need me.

27:00.568 --> 27:02.590
It's good to feel needed.

27:03.831 --> 27:04.973
I like to feel needed.

27:05.053 --> 27:09.297
I like to think that the work that I do is a necessary kind of work.

27:09.377 --> 27:11.339
I like to think that it helps people.

27:11.780 --> 27:18.227
I like to think that hopefully it adds some joy to people's lives or some comfort to people's lives.

27:18.267 --> 27:21.791
We all have an innate need to be needed.

27:22.912 --> 27:24.754
But that can go too far.

27:25.282 --> 27:32.674
to where, again, your entire personality, the entire part of your being is wrapped up in, people need me.

27:33.015 --> 27:34.898
People need to be dependent on me.

27:35.419 --> 27:37.903
People need me to be there.

27:38.604 --> 27:40.607
And so you can't let anything go.

27:40.647 --> 27:43.172
You can't turn over the keys.

27:43.853 --> 27:48.240
Your desire to be needed overwhelms everything else.

27:50.684 --> 27:51.826
These are convicting.

27:55.586 --> 28:02.315
The fourth is I have a certain level of wealth, financial freedom, and very nice possessions.

28:02.395 --> 28:05.239
And we all know, and I'm not going to beat this horse to death yet.

28:05.299 --> 28:06.581
I'll do that later in this sermon.

28:07.001 --> 28:12.789
But materialism, idolatry, I mean, we live in it, right?

28:12.949 --> 28:22.322
I think I read an article that said the average home in the United States has over 200,000 pieces in it of stuff.

28:23.074 --> 28:27.599
I got stuff in my garage in boxes lined almost to the ceiling.

28:27.799 --> 28:30.722
I couldn't even tell you what is in any of those boxes.

28:31.323 --> 28:44.077
If somebody came to me and said, hey, I think I left such and such in a box out there, it would literally take me all week to go through all the boxes of the junk that's in my garage to find what it is that they might be looking for.

28:44.217 --> 28:48.722
I mean, we have and love our possessions.

28:48.930 --> 28:55.776
And we always think, you know, I might need that little ruler that I found at a garage sale for a nickel 25 years ago.

28:55.856 --> 28:58.779
So I'm going to carry it with me for the rest of my life.

29:04.384 --> 29:14.494
Well, family idolatry, my children and or my parents are happy and they are happy with me.

29:14.514 --> 29:18.898
You know, family is probably one of the biggest.

29:20.258 --> 29:23.663
tricks that Satan uses, right?

29:23.723 --> 29:25.065
Because it's such a good thing.

29:26.728 --> 29:39.247
You know, we'll take our kid to travel sports and, you know, he won't be able to go to church on Sunday for, you know, sick for years because he's gonna be playing games every Sunday.

29:39.908 --> 29:45.517
And it's such a good idea that, oh man, in the rationalizations can flow from there.

29:45.557 --> 29:47.159
Oh man, I'm doing a good thing here.

29:47.219 --> 29:49.042
This is a good thing for my kid.

29:49.154 --> 29:54.323
You know, and I'm not telling you how to raise your kids because, you know, I've, I get it, man.

29:54.403 --> 29:57.327
It's the hardest job in the entire world is to raise a child.

29:58.249 --> 30:02.576
But we have to be careful as moms and dads that our children don't become our idols.

30:05.180 --> 30:07.484
You can have relationship idolatry, right?

30:07.544 --> 30:08.306
Mr or Mrs.

30:08.386 --> 30:09.728
Right is in love with me.

30:09.768 --> 30:13.294
And that gives my life purpose and that gives my life meaning.

30:14.416 --> 30:15.858
You know, I heard about a fellow that,

30:16.354 --> 30:21.405
I went to talk to his rabbi and he said, Rabbi, I have a strong desire to live for eternity.

30:22.587 --> 30:24.111
The rabbi says, well, that's easy.

30:24.191 --> 30:25.033
Just get married.

30:27.779 --> 30:32.890
And he says, it's really that simple that that would allow me to live forever.

30:33.731 --> 30:36.818
And the rabbi said, not really, but the desire will disappear.

30:45.154 --> 30:47.698
And so we can have a relationship idolatry.

30:49.059 --> 30:54.387
We can have achievement idolatry, which is very prevalent in our culture today.

30:54.447 --> 30:57.171
America loves winners.

30:58.532 --> 30:59.434
We celebrate them.

31:00.635 --> 31:03.419
We commercialize them.

31:04.160 --> 31:05.542
We write books about them.

31:06.523 --> 31:10.148
I mean, probably, in fact, we're so infatuated with it.

31:10.168 --> 31:14.194
There's probably a good number of people in this room,

31:14.370 --> 31:25.200
including me that couldn't tell you who the losing team was in the Super Bowl last year, or who the losing team was in the NCAA basketball tournament, right?

31:25.261 --> 31:32.347
Because we were so focused on celebrating winners that achievement can become an idol.

31:34.810 --> 31:43.378
And then we can have a suffering idolatry, which says, my life only has meaning or I only have worth if I'm hurting.

31:44.642 --> 31:45.563
or in a problem.

31:46.765 --> 31:49.930
Only then do I feel worthy or loved.

31:50.611 --> 31:56.579
Only then do I feel like I'm able to deal with guilt when I'm suffering.

31:58.902 --> 32:01.286
You know, these things can slip into our lives.

32:02.548 --> 32:12.562
And I would imagine that if these eight, you've probably seen at least some warning signs in some of them for your own life, as I know I did for mine.

32:13.698 --> 32:21.250
You know, none of us sit here and actively think of the phrase, my life only has meaning or I only have worth or value if I fill in the blank.

32:22.392 --> 32:27.640
Instead, right, it's the way that we live our lives that reveals the throne on our heart.

32:28.341 --> 32:35.653
We don't sit there and say my life only has meaning and value if I have a new car or a new phone or if I'm dressed in the latest fashion.

32:36.254 --> 32:41.202
Instead, we just drive ourselves into debt over stuff that doesn't ultimately matter.

32:41.666 --> 32:45.750
And in doing so, we reveal what's on the throne of our heart.

32:47.672 --> 32:52.336
But everything I listed here is a surface idol.

32:53.898 --> 32:56.860
What are some of the real root idols?

33:01.865 --> 33:05.228
Well, some of the root idols are these.

33:06.229 --> 33:11.154
Comfort idolatry, power idolatry, approval idolatry,

33:11.362 --> 33:13.404
and control idolatry.

33:16.087 --> 33:25.056
Comfort idolatry says, my life has meaning or value if I have this kind of pleasure or experience or a particular quality of life.

33:26.798 --> 33:32.523
It's no surprise that if you worship a comfort idol, that comfort is the thing that you want.

33:33.404 --> 33:34.485
They want privacy.

33:34.525 --> 33:35.907
They want a lack of stress.

33:35.987 --> 33:36.868
They want freedom.

33:36.908 --> 33:39.090
And this oftentimes

33:39.618 --> 33:51.076
comes across as being really laid back and easy going, but it's at the cost of any kind of productivity because their greatest nightmare is encountering stress or demands.

33:52.418 --> 33:53.821
Now, maybe you're thinking, well, that's good.

33:53.841 --> 33:56.084
That's not me, but hold on, I'll get to you.

33:58.889 --> 34:02.414
But for the person who worships comfort, that's the worst.

34:02.434 --> 34:03.516
Stress and demands.

34:03.556 --> 34:04.778
That's the big nightmare.

34:05.780 --> 34:07.282
But here's the thing, right?

34:08.130 --> 34:11.054
is that it often leaves others feeling neglected and hurt.

34:12.397 --> 34:24.335
Because when we're lazy above all else, when we pay the price of productivity for comfort, somebody else always gets hurt because they feel like they don't matter.

34:26.298 --> 34:33.289
When I say I'll get around to that sometime and then I never get around to it, it makes people feel like they don't matter.

34:34.871 --> 34:36.754
And the biggest problem of motion

34:37.218 --> 34:44.147
that these people experience is boredom because we're not designed to sit around and do nothing all day every day.

34:45.189 --> 34:47.131
The Bible says, Satan loves idle hands.

34:47.231 --> 34:57.325
Colossians says, whatever you do, work hardly, ask for the Lord and not from in, knowing that from the Lord, you will receive the inheritance as your reward.

34:57.986 --> 34:59.848
You are serving the Lord Christ.

35:01.711 --> 35:07.218
We all believers, we glorify God by how we live our lives for Him.

35:07.778 --> 35:11.442
and not allowing the enemy to take a foothold in boredom.

35:14.925 --> 35:17.368
And it's more than just relationships that suffer.

35:18.349 --> 35:20.051
It's also our work that suffers.

35:21.893 --> 35:25.476
They get taken in conversations, being exposed and vulnerable.

35:25.516 --> 35:35.026
They bounce from person to person, never getting into a relationship that's any deeper than the surface level because they want their comfort above all else.

35:36.482 --> 35:38.344
Comfort makes a terrible God.

35:39.966 --> 35:47.015
The power idolatry is my life only has meaning if I have power and influence over others.

35:48.096 --> 35:49.478
This is a sneaky one too.

35:49.538 --> 35:54.384
Worshiping success, winning, gaining influence.

35:56.106 --> 36:00.451
And more than not, these worshipers are willing to pay the burden of responsibility.

36:00.832 --> 36:01.913
They'll say, I'll bear it.

36:02.033 --> 36:03.175
I'll go through the trenches.

36:03.275 --> 36:03.936
I'll handle it.

36:04.256 --> 36:05.938
If I can get more success,

36:06.178 --> 36:08.901
then I'll handle it and sacrifice anything for it.

36:10.783 --> 36:19.211
So we become willing to pay that price and that weight of responsibility to the point that the major fear becomes humiliation.

36:21.353 --> 36:24.176
When you worship success, it's not just about winning.

36:24.196 --> 36:26.438
It's about not losing.

36:27.559 --> 36:34.546
And the more times that more times than not results in other people feeling used or manipulated,

36:34.626 --> 36:44.858
Because you use people as a means for your own power and your own success and your own ability to control other people or try to control other people.

36:45.578 --> 36:53.127
Worshiping success makes you feel like their relationship with you is just necessary to help you get where you need to go.

36:53.147 --> 37:00.255
And when you get to where you need to go, then you can discard those relationships from the past.

37:01.597 --> 37:02.898
This guy here on the

37:03.074 --> 37:08.442
with the Philadelphia, ugly Philadelphia Eagles uniform.

37:09.163 --> 37:15.592
He went to another high school than I did, but it was our main rival.

37:16.073 --> 37:17.935
So this guy's name is Bobby Taylor.

37:18.476 --> 37:20.399
So Bobby Taylor was 1992.

37:21.160 --> 37:23.123
He graduated from Longview High School.

37:23.603 --> 37:31.154
Longview High School was the main rival, and you're gonna gasp when you hear the name of my high school, but you have to remember I went to high school in the South,

37:31.522 --> 37:34.065
My high school was Robert E. Lee High School.

37:36.848 --> 37:38.650
And we played Longview.

37:39.391 --> 37:43.235
And I remember, man, as a freshman, we hear about this kid, Bobby Taylor.

37:44.056 --> 37:48.020
And we get out there, and we're doing our little warm-ups.

37:48.360 --> 37:52.705
And we're bebop in the line, and we're shooting lay-ups and stuff.

37:52.725 --> 38:00.754
And this guy comes out as a freshman and does a 360 slam dunk in warm-ups.

38:01.826 --> 38:08.353
And at that point, I knew that all my power was gone, right?

38:09.274 --> 38:26.514
By the time he gets to be a senior, he is the Texas State 6A football and basketball player of the year, has a scholarship to play at Notre Dame, both basketball and football, but winds up in football,

38:26.722 --> 38:30.387
and becomes an all-pro-cornerback for the Philadelphia Eagles.

38:30.447 --> 38:35.554
I mean, he was absolutely the best athlete I have ever seen in my life.

38:35.574 --> 38:37.316
He was totally different.

38:38.538 --> 38:41.782
And we knew we had to compete against him and we knew we were gonna lose.

38:44.145 --> 38:47.410
But the Bible doesn't forbid competition, right?

38:48.311 --> 38:52.957
But our drive for success can get out of whack.

38:52.977 --> 38:56.402
And so there's also approval, idolatry.

38:56.994 --> 39:02.061
This says, my life only has worth or value if I am loved and respected.

39:04.184 --> 39:05.806
We want affirmation.

39:05.906 --> 39:07.128
We want relationship.

39:07.168 --> 39:08.730
We want love.

39:09.691 --> 39:13.015
But the cost of it is independence.

39:13.055 --> 39:16.881
We become so dependent on others and their approval of us.

39:17.902 --> 39:22.688
And that's where we get our worth in life, that our greatest fear becomes rejection.

39:23.750 --> 39:26.994
And as such, they'll make others feel smothered because they can't

39:27.234 --> 39:30.218
humanly love you the way that God can love you.

39:31.981 --> 39:34.003
It can take the shape of people pleasing.

39:34.865 --> 39:37.568
You know, maybe with one group, you say, that's a great idea.

39:37.588 --> 39:44.578
And then you get another group and they have a different idea and you say, yeah, those bozos over there, you wouldn't believe what they were saying, right?

39:46.901 --> 39:51.548
At the end of the day, you have to sleep with the knowledge that, you know what, I really disagree with that.

39:52.429 --> 39:56.114
But if I voice my opinion, then I'm going to lose their approval.

39:56.866 --> 39:59.750
And if I lose their approval, well, what if they don't like me anymore?

40:03.355 --> 40:05.638
And then the final one is control idolatry.

40:07.019 --> 40:08.341
And this one's a bad one too.

40:08.401 --> 40:16.452
My life only has worth their value if I'm able to get mastery over it in a particular area.

40:18.134 --> 40:21.558
Those who worship control, you guessed it, seek control.

40:21.619 --> 40:24.242
More specifically,

40:24.674 --> 40:29.161
You may find yourself seeking self-discipline, certainty, standards.

40:29.721 --> 40:32.265
These thoughts have prepared everything for the trip.

40:32.325 --> 40:37.173
I know the weather for every day of the week, down to the hour, and I'll have everything that I need.

40:39.576 --> 40:46.286
Where I've read all the articles I could find about going to the beach, and someone died at the same beach we're going to, and now I'm not gonna get in the water.

40:46.326 --> 40:48.429
In fact, I don't think anybody should get in the water.

40:50.432 --> 40:52.275
Or no one will ever be in any danger.

40:52.375 --> 40:54.418
Danger will not exist in this family.

40:55.202 --> 40:59.368
Is this all consuming desire to control everything?

40:59.408 --> 41:08.039
And what others come away with is they often feel condemned or judged or offended and it results in loneliness, right?

41:08.159 --> 41:22.098
If you can't let go the idea that you are in control of everything, then you will wind up alone because everybody will eventually leave.

41:23.874 --> 41:31.224
A phrase that so commonly comes out of the mouth of a control worshiper is if you would only just, right?

41:31.264 --> 41:35.890
If you'd only just get your act together, then that wouldn't have happened.

41:35.910 --> 41:47.905
But at the heart of the matter is they worry and it's a vicious cycle because worry leads to seeking to control things, but then ultimately we can't, we realize we can't control things.

41:49.447 --> 41:51.570
And so we start to worry about it again.

41:52.098 --> 42:00.773
which leads us to control it again, which leads us right back into the cycle and it just repeats itself over and over and over.

42:02.976 --> 42:06.042
So what's the cure for idolatry?

42:07.985 --> 42:11.210
The cure in Exodus 32 was fast and it was severe.

42:11.311 --> 42:18.002
It said that Moses burned the calf and grounded the powder and scattered it in the water and made the Israelites drink it.

42:19.330 --> 42:20.652
You know why he made him drink it?

42:20.772 --> 42:27.182
I think he made him drink it because he was saying to them, you think this satisfies and fills your hunger.

42:28.003 --> 42:30.707
All right then, eat it and tell me.

42:31.889 --> 42:35.594
Does it satisfy your hunger the way that God does?

42:37.257 --> 42:38.839
There's a call for cleansing there.

42:40.201 --> 42:49.074
In 1 Corinthians 10, he says, there is no testing that has taken you that is not common to everyone, but God is faithful and he will not allow you to be tested

42:49.186 --> 42:55.858
beyond your strengths, but will with the testing also provide a way out so that you may be able to endure it.

42:56.840 --> 43:03.092
And immediately on the heels of that verse, he says, therefore my friends flee from the worship of idols.

43:03.152 --> 43:10.165
Now we oftentimes read the first part of verse 13, but not the second part of verse 13, right?

43:10.245 --> 43:13.170
This passage is talking about idolatry.

43:14.114 --> 43:22.465
And we often apply it to people who suffer and we tell them, well, you know, God says he won't put more on you than you can bear without providing an escape route.

43:22.485 --> 43:23.326
Well, that's not true.

43:23.466 --> 43:26.891
God will absolutely put more on you than you can bear.

43:26.951 --> 43:30.296
That is not what the Bible teaches.

43:31.697 --> 43:35.122
He does that because not because he's sadistic.

43:35.714 --> 43:45.645
or anything like that, he does that because he is going to deliver us and when he delivers us, he wants us to know beyond the shadow of it out that it was him who did it.

43:46.887 --> 43:59.341
If our ushers would come forward and begin to pass out the elements for the Lord's Supper, you know, the first thing that we have to do is not allow that altar to be built.

44:02.224 --> 44:04.146
And that's why we need Christian community.

44:05.346 --> 44:15.159
Remember that they resorted to idolatry because they thought that Moses, who represented the presence of God, wasn't coming back.

44:17.502 --> 44:19.624
And that temptation is the same for us.

44:21.407 --> 44:31.660
When we get out of Christian community, then we can easily become tempted to think that God is not going to hear from me anymore, that God has left me.

44:32.020 --> 44:33.202
He has deserted me.

44:34.146 --> 44:42.817
But when we are in Christian community, it's a lot, we begin to experience the presence of God on a more regular basis.

44:43.478 --> 44:43.758
Why?

44:44.459 --> 44:47.042
Because we're hanging around where the action is happening.

44:48.965 --> 44:49.265
Right?

44:50.246 --> 45:02.802
I mean, if I play in right field, I don't have to, I'm not gonna get every ball hit to me in right field, but I'm gonna get some of them, but I'm sure not gonna be able to play right field if I don't even show up at the ballpark.

45:04.194 --> 45:17.830
Now listen, the live stream is a great thing and I think it's a wonderful and a lot of people listen to it and a lot of people that can't be here in person are able to watch it online when they're traveling or whatever and that's a great thing.

45:17.850 --> 45:30.706
I mean in general, our culture has devalued the idea of the importance of Christian community and you have literally hundreds of thousands, if not millions of people out there

45:30.818 --> 45:34.763
who do not see a reason to gather with other believers on Sunday.

45:35.184 --> 45:43.274
And yeah, you can download the best preachers and you can download this and that and you can create your own little custom worship service at home.

45:43.715 --> 45:47.339
But the Christian life is designed to be lived in Christian community.

45:47.700 --> 45:55.970
And the way to keep those idols off the throne of your life is to be in fellowship with other believers who can see the idols when you're blind to them.

45:57.592 --> 45:58.834
It's as simple as that.

46:00.354 --> 46:17.611
John White said in his book, The Golden Calf, he said, we have overvalued these calves that we worship and we have underestimated and taken for granted and forgotten the God of power that we love and profess to worship.

46:17.631 --> 46:23.496
Psalm 106, 21 says, they worship the golden calf because they forgot God.

46:25.458 --> 46:29.522
Listen friends, as we get ready to take the Lord's Supper today,

46:29.858 --> 46:36.248
The Lord's Supper is a reminder as we take it in community that God has promised.

46:36.969 --> 46:38.411
Jesus is coming back.

46:40.254 --> 46:42.597
He is coming back as the victorious King.

46:42.697 --> 46:45.121
He is coming back as our Lord and our Savior.

46:45.402 --> 46:53.293
That trumpet is going to sound and people are going to rise up out of their graves and it is going to be the greatest thing, right?

46:54.295 --> 46:56.639
Because God does what He says He's going to do.

46:57.500 --> 46:58.962
But until that day,

47:00.002 --> 47:02.225
We ought to constantly examine ourselves.

47:02.265 --> 47:16.141
Are there any of these idols that I need to get off the throne of my life that I need to remove so that God is placed in his correct position?

47:17.482 --> 47:27.794
I want you to take a moment and analyze, contemplate your own life and where you're at in this.

47:27.874 --> 47:32.781
No judgment, it's not an exercise designed to beat anybody down.

47:33.242 --> 47:35.465
It simply is that we're in community.

47:35.926 --> 47:45.500
We have a moment of quietness without our cell phones going off every 13 seconds or whatever, and we're able to examine ourselves.

47:45.560 --> 47:49.746
And I just want to give you a minute to do that before we take the Lord's Supper.

48:30.690 --> 48:34.015
Taking the bread, Jesus said, this is my body, which is broken for you.

48:34.596 --> 48:36.298
Do this in remembrance of me.

48:44.970 --> 48:50.118
Taking the cup, Jesus said, this is my blood, which is spilled for the forgiveness of sin.

48:51.039 --> 48:53.202
Do this in remembrance of me.

48:59.298 --> 49:00.760
You need to do business with God.

49:00.800 --> 49:05.326
The worship team is going to come and lead us in a song.

49:06.548 --> 49:07.729
You pray where you're at.

49:07.909 --> 49:09.892
You grab somebody and pray with them.

49:10.253 --> 49:11.875
You come to the altar and pray.

49:12.716 --> 49:17.062
You do the business with God that he has called you to do today.

49:20.847 --> 49:21.367
Let's pray.

49:22.709 --> 49:26.214
Father, we thank you, God, for your goodness, for your mercy, and for your grace.

49:27.135 --> 49:29.298
We're going to help us not to worship idols.

49:30.306 --> 49:38.541
Not to worship comfort or approval or power or control God.

49:40.464 --> 49:44.432
You are on the throne of our hearts and that is where you belong.

49:45.794 --> 49:48.940
So mold us and shape us God for it's in Christ's name we pray.

49:49.701 --> 49:50.162
Amen.

